HOUSE BILL 1182
F1 6lr3525
By: Delegate McCaskill Delegates McCaskill, Ebersole, Feldmark, Griffith, Miller,
Mireku–North, Palakovich Carr, Pasteur, Patterson, Wilkins, and Wims
Introduced and read first time: February 11, 2026
Assigned to: Ways and Means
Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
House action: Adopted
Read second time: March 4, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Public and Nonpublic Schools – Student Elopement – Locative Devices
3 FOR the purpose of requiring certain public and nonpublic schools to develop policies and
4 procedures regarding student wandering or elopement behavior; authorizing certain
5 public and nonpublic schools to coordinate a student’s voluntary use of a certain
6 locative device and monitor the student’s location using the locative device for certain
7 purposes and under certain circumstances; establishing certain privacy and data
8 protections for information obtained through a student’s voluntary use of a certain
9 locative device; requiring the State Department of Education to issue certain
10 advisory guidance to certain public and nonpublic schools; and generally relating to
11 student wandering and elopement behavior.
12 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
13 Article – Education
14 Section 7–11A–01 and 7–11A–02
15 Annotated Code of Maryland
16 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
17 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
18 Article – Education
19 Section 7–11A–02
20 Annotated Code of Maryland
21 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
